az_dict = dict()
i = 0
with open('Azimuth_Cell_Types_2021_edited_parent_VR_editNaive.csv') as file:
    for line in file:
        i += 1
        split = line.rstrip().split('\t')
        az_dict[split[1]] = [x for x in split[3:] if x != '']

Run first iter GSEA¶

In [19]:
cl_gname = 'leiden_r1'
rank_name = 'rank_genes_r1'
groups = adata.obs[cl_gname].cat.categories.tolist()
gsea_res = dict()
pred = dict()
pred_overlap = dict()
pred_2 = dict()
pred_2_overlap = dict()
pred_2 = dict()
pval = dict()
pval_2 = dict()
pconf = dict()

groups_anno_df = pd.DataFrame(data={cl_gname:groups,
                                    'cell_counts':adata.obs[cl_gname].value_counts().tolist()})

db='az'

for cl in groups:
    print(cl)
    glist = sc.get.rank_genes_groups_df(adata, 
                                        group=cl, 
                                        pval_cutoff=0.05,
                                        key=rank_name,
                                        log2fc_min=1.5)['names'].squeeze().str.strip().tolist()
    if len(glist) > 100:
        glist = glist[:100]
    enr_res = gseapy.enrichr(gene_list=glist,
             # or gene_list=glist
             gene_sets=az_dict,
             background= adata.raw.shape[1], # or the number of genes, e.g 20000
             cutoff=0.01, # only used for testing.
             verbose=True,
             description='pathway',
             no_plot=True,
             top_term=10)
    if enr_res.results.shape[0] == 0:
        pred[cl] = "unassigned"
    else:
        enr_res.results.sort_values(by="Adjusted P-value",axis=0, ascending=True, inplace=True)
#         if enr_res.results.iloc[0,4] > 0.01:
#             pred[cl] = "unassigned"
#             continue
        gsea_res[cl]=enr_res
        pred[cl] = enr_res.results.iloc[0,1]
        pred_2[cl] = enr_res.results.iloc[1,1]
        pval[cl] = enr_res.results.iloc[0,4]
        pval_2[cl] = enr_res.results.iloc[1,4]
        pred_overlap[cl] = enr_res.results.iloc[0,5]
        pred_2_overlap[cl] = enr_res.results.iloc[1,5]
        pconf[cl] = np.abs(np.log10(enr_res.results.iloc[0,4])) - np.abs(np.log10(enr_res.results.iloc[1,4]))
        
    # add to cluster table
    groups_anno_df[db] = groups_anno_df[cl_gname].map(pred)
    groups_anno_df[db + '_overlap'] = groups_anno_df[cl_gname].map(pred_overlap)
    groups_anno_df[db + '_2'] = groups_anno_df[cl_gname].map(pred_2)
    groups_anno_df[db + '_overlap2'] = groups_anno_df[cl_gname].map(pred_2_overlap)
    groups_anno_df[db + '_parent'] = groups_anno_df[db].map(az_parent_dict)
    groups_anno_df[db + '_parent2'] = groups_anno_df[db + '_2'].map(az_parent_dict)
    groups_anno_df[db + '_PVAL'] = groups_anno_df[cl_gname].map(pval).astype('float64')
    groups_anno_df[db + '_PVAL2'] = groups_anno_df[cl_gname].map(pval_2).astype('float64')
    groups_anno_df[db + '_PCONF'] = groups_anno_df[cl_gname].map(pconf).astype('float64')

    # add to cells
    adata.obs[db] = adata.obs[cl_gname].map(pred)

#1) if confidence > 1, assign

groups_anno_df.loc[groups_anno_df['az_PCONF'] > 1, 'final_pred'] = groups_anno_df.loc[groups_anno_df['az_PCONF'] > 1, 'az']

#2) if confidence is low but parents are the same, assign parent

groups_anno_df.loc[(groups_anno_df['final_pred'] == 'unassigned') & 
                   (groups_anno_df['az_parent'] == groups_anno_df['az_parent2']), 'final_pred'] = groups_anno_df.loc[(groups_anno_df['final_pred'] == 'unassigned') & 
                                                                                                                     (groups_anno_df['az_parent'] == groups_anno_df['az_parent2']), 'az_parent']

#3) if confidence is low and first hit is a broad cell type, give assign to second hit

groups_anno_df.loc[(groups_anno_df['final_pred'] == 'unassigned') & 
                   (groups_anno_df['az'].str.contains('Broad')) &
                    (groups_anno_df['az_parent'] == groups_anno_df['az_parent2'].str.split(' ').str[1]), 'final_pred'] = groups_anno_df.loc[(groups_anno_df['final_pred'] == 'unassigned') & 
                                                                                                                                   (groups_anno_df['az'].str.contains('Broad')) &
                                                                                                                                   (groups_anno_df['az_parent'] == groups_anno_df['az_parent2'].str.split(' ').str[1]), 'az_2']

#4 if still un-assigned and both are T cells, give it T

                    (groups_anno_df['az_parent'].str.split(' ').str[1] == groups_anno_df['az_parent2'].str.split(' ').str[1]), 'final_pred'] = 'T'

Recursive GSEA function¶

In [27]:
def gsea(adata, all_sub, keep_subclus, cell_counts, cl_gname, groups_anno_df_final):
    print(keep_subclus)
    
    filter_sub = [x for x in all_sub if x != keep_subclus]
#     print(filter_sub)

    adata_new = adata[~adata.obs[cl_gname].isin(filter_sub),:].copy()
    print(adata_new.shape)
    rank_name = 'rank_genes_' + keep_subclus.replace(',','')
    sc.tl.rank_genes_groups(adata_new, groupby=cl_gname,key_added=rank_name)
        
    gsea_res = dict()
    pred = dict()
    pred_overlap = dict()
    pred_2 = dict()
    pred_2_overlap = dict()
    final_pred = dict()
    pval = dict()
    pval_2 = dict()
    pconf = dict()

    groups_anno_df = pd.DataFrame(data={'groups':[keep_subclus],
                                        'cell_counts': [cell_counts]})

    db='az_final'
    
    # get adata inds
    cell_inds = adata_new.obs[adata_new.obs[cl_gname] == keep_subclus].index
    
    # rank genes

    rank_genes_groups_df = sc.get.rank_genes_groups_df(adata_new, 
                                        group=keep_subclus, 
                                        pval_cutoff=0.05,
                                        key=rank_name,
                                        log2fc_min=1.5)
    print(rank_genes_groups_df.shape)
    if rank_genes_groups_df.shape[0] == 0:
        print('No ranked genes')
        final_pred[keep_subclus] = "No ranked genes"
        adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_cluster'] = keep_subclus
        adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_prediction'] = adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_cluster'].map(final_pred)
        
        groups_anno_df[db + '_prediction'] = 'No ranked genes'
        groups_anno_df_final = pd.concat([groups_anno_df_final,groups_anno_df])
        return final_pred[keep_subclus], groups_anno_df_final
    
    try:
        glist = rank_genes_groups_df['names'].squeeze().str.strip().tolist()
    except AttributeError:
        print('AttributeError')
        final_pred[keep_subclus] = "AttributeError"
        adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_cluster'] = keep_subclus
        adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_prediction'] = adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_cluster'].map(final_pred)
        groups_anno_df[db + '_prediction'] = 'AttributeError'
        groups_anno_df_final = pd.concat([groups_anno_df_final,groups_anno_df])
        return final_pred[keep_subclus], groups_anno_df_final
    
    if len(glist) > 100:
        glist = glist[:100]
    enr_res = gseapy.enrichr(gene_list=glist,
             # or gene_list=glist
             gene_sets=az_dict,
             background= adata.raw.shape[1], # or the number of genes, e.g 20000
             cutoff=0.01, # only used for testing.
             verbose=True,
             description='pathway',
             no_plot=True,
             top_term=10)
    if enr_res.results.shape[0] == 0:
        print('No significant hits')
        pred[keep_subclus] = "No significant hits"
        final_pred[keep_subclus] = "No significant hits"
        groups_anno_df[db + '_prediction'] = groups_anno_df['groups'].map(final_pred)
        groups_anno_df_final = pd.concat([groups_anno_df_final,groups_anno_df])
        adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_cluster'] = keep_subclus
        adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_prediction'] = adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_cluster'].map(final_pred)
        return final_pred[keep_subclus], groups_anno_df_final
    else:
        enr_res.results.sort_values(by="Adjusted P-value",axis=0, ascending=True, inplace=True)
        if enr_res.results.iloc[0,4] > 0.01:
            final_pred[keep_subclus] = "unassigned"

        gsea_res[keep_subclus]=enr_res
        pred[keep_subclus] = enr_res.results.iloc[0,1]
        pred_2[keep_subclus] = enr_res.results.iloc[1,1]
        pval[keep_subclus] = enr_res.results.iloc[0,4]
        pval_2[keep_subclus] = enr_res.results.iloc[1,4]
        pred_overlap[keep_subclus] = enr_res.results.iloc[0,5]
        pred_2_overlap[keep_subclus] = enr_res.results.iloc[1,5]
        pconf[keep_subclus] = np.abs(np.log10(enr_res.results.iloc[0,4])) - np.abs(np.log10(enr_res.results.iloc[1,4]))
        
        str1 = re.sub(r'\d? CL.*$','',pred[keep_subclus]).rstrip()
        str2 = re.sub(r'\d? CL.*$','',pred_2[keep_subclus]).rstrip()

        if pconf[keep_subclus] > 1:
            final_pred[keep_subclus] = pred[keep_subclus]
        elif str1 == str2:
            # eg. CD8+ Effector Memory T CL0001050 and CD8+ Effector Memory T 2 CL0001050
            pred[keep_subclus] = str1
            final_pred[keep_subclus] = pred[keep_subclus]
        else:
            final_pred[keep_subclus] = "unassigned"

        # add to cluster table
        groups_anno_df[db] = groups_anno_df['groups'].map(pred)
        groups_anno_df[db + '_overlap'] = groups_anno_df['groups'].map(pred_overlap)
        groups_anno_df[db + '_2'] = groups_anno_df['groups'].map(pred_2)
        groups_anno_df[db + '_overlap2'] = groups_anno_df['groups'].map(pred_2_overlap)
        groups_anno_df[db + '_PVAL'] = groups_anno_df['groups'].map(pval).astype('float64')
        groups_anno_df[db + '_PVAL2'] = groups_anno_df['groups'].map(pval_2).astype('float64')
        groups_anno_df[db + '_PCONF'] = groups_anno_df['groups'].map(pconf).astype('float64')
        groups_anno_df[db + '_prediction'] = groups_anno_df['groups'].map(final_pred)
        
        groups_anno_df_final = pd.concat([groups_anno_df_final,groups_anno_df])
        
        # add to adata
        adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_cluster'] = keep_subclus
        adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db] = adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_cluster'].map(pred)
        adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_2'] = adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_cluster'].map(pred_2)
        adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_PVAL'] = adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_cluster'].map(pval).astype('float64')
        adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_PVAL2'] = adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_cluster'].map(pval_2).astype('float64')
        adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_overlap'] = adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_cluster'].map(pred_overlap)
        adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_overlap2'] = adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_cluster'].map(pred_2_overlap)
        adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_PCONF'] = adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_cluster'].map(pconf).astype('float64')
        adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_prediction'] = adata.obs.loc[cell_inds, db + '_cluster'].map(final_pred)
        
    return final_pred[keep_subclus], groups_anno_df_final

def recur_clus(adata, orig_cl_gname, orig_cells_val_cnts, subclus, cl_gname, clus_cells, groups_anno_df_final, final_pred):
    parent_clus = subclus.split(',')[0]
    parent_cnt = orig_cells_val_cnts.loc[parent_clus]
    pct = clus_cells/parent_cnt
    if pct < 0.10 or final_pred != 'unassigned':
        print('stopping at ' + subclus)
        return groups_anno_df_final
    else:
        sc.tl.leiden(adata, restrict_to=(orig_cl_gname, [subclus]), resolution=1, key_added=cl_gname)
        orig_cl_gname =  deepcopy(cl_gname)
        val_cnts = adata.obs[cl_gname].value_counts()
        all_sub = val_cnts[val_cnts.index.str.contains(subclus + ',')].index.tolist()
        cl_gname = 'groups00'
        for keep_subclus in all_sub:
#             cl_gname = 'groups' + keep_subclus.replace(',','')
            # leiden will keep going even if it can't break down
            if clus_cells == val_cnts.loc[keep_subclus] and keep_subclus[:-2] == subclus and ',' in subclus:
                print(keep_subclus,subclus)
#                 groups_anno_df_final = groups_anno_df_final[groups_anno_df_final['groups'] != keep_subclus]
                print('stopping at ' + subclus)
                continue
            clus_cells = val_cnts.loc[keep_subclus]
            final_pred, groups_anno_df_final = gsea(adata, all_sub, keep_subclus, clus_cells, orig_cl_gname, groups_anno_df_final)
            groups_anno_df_final = recur_clus(adata, orig_cl_gname, orig_cells_val_cnts, keep_subclus, cl_gname, clus_cells, groups_anno_df_final, final_pred)
    return groups_anno_df_final

# find low level clusters that are unassigned to rescue
unassigned = groups_anno_df_final[groups_anno_df_final['az_final_prediction'] == 'unassigned'].copy()
unassigned

unassigned['count_commas'] = unassigned['groups'].str.count(',')
unassigned['parent'] = unassigned['groups'].str.split(',').str[0]
unassigned

lowest_groups = []
for p in unassigned['parent'].unique():
    max_count = unassigned.loc[unassigned['parent'] == p,'count_commas'].max()
    for x in unassigned.loc[(unassigned['parent'] == p) & (unassigned['groups'].str.count(',') == max_count),'groups'].values:
        lowest_groups.append(x)
        
rescue_df = groups_anno_df_final[groups_anno_df_final['groups'].isin(lowest_groups)]

db='az_final'
rescue_df['orig_cluster'] = rescue_df['groups'].str.split(',').str[0]
rescue_df['orig_anno'] = rescue_df['orig_cluster'].map(firstanno_dict)
rescue_df[db + '_parent'] = rescue_df[db].map(az_parent_dict)
rescue_df[db + '_parent2'] = rescue_df[db + '_2'].map(az_parent_dict)
rescue_df

#1) rescue CD4+ T and CD8 + T eg. CD8+ T Cell 1 CL0000625 and CD8+ Effector Memory T CL0001050

rescue_df.loc[rescue_df[db].str.split(' ').str[0] == rescue_df[db + '_2'].str.split(' ').str[0], db + '_prediction'] = rescue_df.loc[rescue_df[db].str.split(' ').str[0] == rescue_df[db + '_2'].str.split(' ').str[0], db].str.split(' ').str[0] + ' T'

#2) if confidence is low but parents are the same, assign parent

rescue_df.loc[
    (rescue_df[db + '_prediction'] == 'unassigned') & \
    (rescue_df[db + '_parent'] == rescue_df[db + '_parent2']), db + '_prediction'] = rescue_df.loc[(rescue_df[db + '_prediction'] == 'unassigned') &
                                                                                                   (rescue_df[db + '_parent'] == rescue_df[db + '_parent2']), db + '_parent']

#3) if confidence is low but original cluster is the same, assign it

rescue_df.loc[(rescue_df[db + '_prediction'] == 'unassigned') & \
              (rescue_df[db] == rescue_df['orig_anno']), db + '_prediction'] =  rescue_df.loc[(rescue_df[db + '_prediction'] == 'unassigned') &
                                                                                             (rescue_df[db] == rescue_df['orig_anno']), 'orig_anno']

#4) if confidence is low and first hit is a broad cell type, give assign to second hit

rescue_df.loc[(rescue_df[db + '_prediction'] == 'unassigned') & 
              (rescue_df[db].str.contains('Broad')) &
              (rescue_df[db + '_parent'] == rescue_df[db + '_parent2'].str.split(' ').str[1]), db + '_prediction'] = rescue_df.loc[(rescue_df[db + '_prediction'] == 'unassigned') & 
                                                                                                                     (rescue_df[db].str.contains('Broad')) &
                                                                                                                     (rescue_df[db + '_parent'] == rescue_df[db + '_parent2'].str.split(' ').str[1]), db + '_parent2']

#5 if still un-assigned and both are T cells, give it T
rescue_df.loc[(rescue_df[db + '_prediction'] == 'unassigned') & 
              (rescue_df[db + '_parent'] == rescue_df[db + '_parent2'].str.split(' ').str[1]), db + '_prediction'] = 'T'
